at the World Cup?\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 5827, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the World Cup\", \"from\": 5813, \"to\": 5826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Can you describe it?\", \"from\": 5828, \"to\": 5848, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alozie:This is so stupid but it was definitely when we had our media day and they were asking us questions and having us put on our different uniforms, and they were sending us photos and explaining what they were going to be for.\", \"from\": 5850, \"to\": 6080, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alozie\", \"from\": 5850, \"to\": 5856}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 5944, \"to\": 5946}, {\"ngram\": \"questions\", \"from\": 5947, \"to\": 5956}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 5970}, {\"ngram\": \"our different uniforms\", \"from\": 5978, \"to\": 6000}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 6024, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 6027, \"to\": 6033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were like 'This is going to be headlining for FIFA,\\\" and I was just [thinking] 'What is going on?'\", \"from\": 6081, \"to\": 6184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6132, \"end\": 6136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.9998397110555387, \"rank\": 0.00010764828341922682, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt like a little celebrity!\", \"from\": 6186, \"to\": 6217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a little celebrity\", \"from\": 6198, \"to\": 6216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This has literally been a dream of mine-my childhood dream!\", \"from\": 6218, \"to\": 6277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a dream\", \"from\": 6242, \"to\": 6249}, {\"ngram\": \"mine\", \"from\": 6253, \"to\": 6257}, {\"ngram\": \"my childhood dream\", \"from\": 6258, \"to\": 6276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was so fulfilled!\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6297, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt like I was able to kind of close a really important chapter from my childhood from that.I love that!\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a really important chapter\", \"from\": 6338, \"to\": 6364}, {\"ngram\": \"my childhood\", \"from\": 6370, \"to\": 6382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are Nigerian by blood.\", \"from\": 6406, \"to\": 6432, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"blood\", \"from\": 6426, \"to\": 6431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What was it like growing up in a Nigerian household as a first-generation American?\", \"from\": 6433, \"to\": 6516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6466, \"end\": 6474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"score\": 0.649460686233179, \"rank\": 0.5311638516044928, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\"}, {\"begin\": 6507, \"end\": 6515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9819776017171225, \"rank\": 0.01079589953722953, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alozie:Yeah, I remember discussing this in college with other first-generation Americans.\", \"from\": 6518, \"to\": 6607, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alozie\", \"from\": 6518, \"to\": 6524}, {\"ngram\": \"college\", \"from\": 6561, \"to\": 6568}, {\"ngram\": \"other first-generation Americans\", \"from\": 6574, \"to\": 6606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it was kind of a state of confusion growing up.\", \"from\": 6608, \"to\": 6663, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"kind of a state\", \"from\": 6623, \"to\": 6638}, {\"ngram\": \"confusion\", \"from\": 6642, \"to\": 6651}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You kind of feel like you are split between two cultures.\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 6721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two cultures\", \"from\": 6708, \"to\": 6720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I remember being almost embarrassed to be African or to be a Nigerian-to smell like the cuisine or to have my parents have the accent, which now I think is just so silly.\", \"from\": 6722, \"to\": 6892, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Nigerian\", \"from\": 6781, \"to\": 6791}, {\"ngram\": \"the cuisine\", \"from\": 6806, \"to\": 6817}, {\"ngram\": \"my parents\", \"from\": 6829, \"to\": 6839}, {\"ngram\": \"the accent\", \"from\": 6845, \"to\": 6855}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I remember it just being a little tough for me, trying to appeal to both cultures.\", \"from\": 6894, \"to\": 6980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"both cultures\", \"from\": 6966, \"to\": 6979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, I feel so sad that I was ever embarrassed by my parents' accents and smelling likeEgusi soupwhen it's really so good and everyone wants to try it now!\", \"from\": 6981, \"to\": 7136, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my parents' accents\", \"from\": 7031, \"to\": 7050}, {\"ngram\": \"soupwhen\", \"from\": 7074, \"to\": 7082}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 7107, \"to\": 7115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I remember it being tough and me not necessarily understanding why it was so hard to be a part of two cultures at the same time.\", \"from\": 7137, \"to\": 7269, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 7229, \"to\": 7235}, {\"ngram\": \"two cultures\", \"from\": 7239, \"to\": 7251}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 7255, \"to\": 7268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you for sharing that!\", \"from\": 7271, \"to\": 7298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What is your full Nigerian name and what does it mean?\", \"from\": 7299, \"to\": 7353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7317, \"end\": 7325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9848930519873683, \"rank\": 0.015169461570214926, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alozie:My name isMichelle Chinwendu Alozie.\", \"from\": 7355, \"to\": 7398, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alozie\", \"from\": 7355, \"to\": 7361}, {\"ngram\": \"My name\", \"from\": 7362, \"to\": 7369}, {\"ngram\": \"isMichelle\", \"from\": 7370, \"to\": 7380}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinwendu Alozie\", \"from\": 7381, \"to\": 7397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chinwendu means \\\"God owns life.\\\"\", \"from\": 7399, \"to\": 7431, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chinwendu\", \"from\": 7399, \"to\": 7408}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 7416, \"to\": 7419}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 7425, \"to\": 7429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think I really show that with the opportunities that I am making for myself and just sticking to it.\", \"from\": 7432, \"to\": 7534, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opportunities\", \"from\": 7464, \"to\": 7481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As you said, when opportunities are not available, you have to make them and I think that God is doing that with me daily, whether I see it or not.\", \"from\": 7535, \"to\": 7682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"opportunities\", \"from\": 7553, \"to\": 7566}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 7625, \"to\": 7628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think I live by my name for sure-my parents did well with that!\", \"from\": 7683, \"to\": 7748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my name\", \"from\": 7701, \"to\": 7708}, {\"ngram\": \"sure-my parents\", \"from\": 7713, \"to\": 7728}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I love that, that's beautiful!\", \"from\": 7750, \"to\": 7780, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A moment ago you talked about growing up and wanting to hide your Nigerian roots, wanting to water down your parents' accents.\", \"from\": 7781, \"to\": 7907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7847, \"end\": 7855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9848930519873683, \"rank\": 0.015169461570214926, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your parents' accents\", \"from\": 7885, \"to\": 7906}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why did it feel so embarrassing back then and what changed for you?\", \"from\": 7908, \"to\": 7975, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alozie:I grew up in a pretty small town so I do not know if people were just a little xenophobic at the time, but being different was just so not okay.\", \"from\": 7977, \"to\": 8128, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alozie\", \"from\": 7977, \"to\": 7983}, {\"ngram\": \"a pretty small town\", \"from\": 7997, \"to\": 8016}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 8037, \"to\": 8043}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 8077, \"to\": 8085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I remember just having a baby identity crisis when I was younger, when people were like, 'Oh, you have never like been to a barbecue or your family does not have cookouts?'\", \"from\": 8129, \"to\": 8301, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a baby identity crisis\", \"from\": 8152, \"to\": 8174}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 8200, \"to\": 8206}, {\"ngram\": \"a barbecue\", \"from\": 8251, \"to\": 8261}, {\"ngram\": \"your family\", \"from\": 8265, \"to\": 8276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I would say 'No, but once a month that Imo population in San Diego will get together and have this big party where we get all dressed up and meet new people. '\", \"from\": 8302, \"to\": 8465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8367, \"end\": 8372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\", \"score\": 0.9069495271064961, \"rank\": 0.10259226018665832, \"text\": \"Diego\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"population\", \"from\": 8349, \"to\": 8359}, {\"ngram\": \"this big party\", \"from\": 8400, \"to\": 8414}, {\"ngram\": \"new people\", \"from\": 8452, \"to\": 8462}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they'd be like 'What are you doing?\", \"from\": 8466, \"to\": 8505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This does not sound right.'\", \"from\": 8506, \"to\": 8533, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I think it was just the fact that I was just so different and it was a part of a culture that a lot of people were not exposed to, especially in my small town in California.\", \"from\": 8535, \"to\": 8712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8701, \"end\": 8711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.9999908447144484, \"rank\": 8.19738895719684e-06, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the fact\", \"from\": 8554, \"to\": 8567}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 8608, \"to\": 8614}, {\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 8618, \"to\": 8627}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 8633, \"to\": 8638}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 8642, \"to\": 8648}, {\"ngram\": \"my small town\", \"from\": 8684, \"to\": 8697}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was just hard for them to understand that yes I am Black.\", \"from\": 8713, \"to\": 8773, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do live in America and have an American accent, but my actual culture is Nigerian.\", \"from\": 8774, \"to\": 8858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8807, \"end\": 8815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6604295905106679, \"rank\": 0.414295090555078, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 8787, \"to\": 8794}, {\"ngram\": \"my actual culture\", \"from\": 8828, \"to\": 8845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My upbringing and what we do in the home are completely different than what your Black American friends do.\", \"from\": 8859, \"to\": 8966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8940, \"end\": 8945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.8988600067334986, \"rank\": 0.10112994754903602, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 8946, \"end\": 8954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6604295905106679, \"rank\": 0.414295090555078, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My upbringing\", \"from\": 8859, \"to\": 8872}, {\"ngram\": \"the home\", \"from\": 8891, \"to\": 8899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we were younger, that was just a little bit difficult for people and myself really to come to grasp.\", \"from\": 8967, \"to\": 9072, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 9030, \"to\": 9036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think it was until really college that I finally met friends who were also first-generation and they all kind of had the same experiences as me growing up, whether it was in New York, Florida, or Charlotte.\", \"from\": 9074, \"to\": 9289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9257, \"end\": 9265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\